{%- comment -%}
  Tooltip (spec §5.3 "Name on hover tooltip").

  Note on approach: this was initially attempted on the native Popover API
  (`popover`/`popovertarget`) to get light-dismiss and Escape-handling for free.
  That turned out to be the wrong tool here — popover content renders in the
  top layer, detached from its trigger's normal containing block, so anchoring it
  directly above/below the trigger would need either CSS anchor positioning
  (too new for reliable cross-browser use today) or manual JS measurement on
  every show. For a small, local, hover-triggered tooltip, plain
  position:relative/absolute (see assets/tooltip.js) is simpler and behaves
  correctly with zero positioning bugs — the right trade-off given the Popover
  API's benefits here were marginal anyway (a hover tooltip already closes on
  mouseleave/blur without needing light-dismiss).

  Accepts:
  - id (required): must be unique per instance on the page (e.g. "swatch-{{ forloop.index }}")
  - trigger (required): captured HTML/text for the visible trigger
  - content (required): tooltip body text
  - position: 'top' (default) | 'bottom'
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign tooltip_position = position | default: 'top'
  assign tooltip_id = 'tooltip-' | append: id
-%}
<span class="tooltip">
  <button type="button" class="tooltip__trigger" aria-describedby="{{ tooltip_id }}">
    {{ trigger }}
  </button>
  <span class="tooltip__content tooltip__content--{{ tooltip_position }}" id="{{ tooltip_id }}" role="tooltip">
    {{ content }}
  </span>
</span>
